cat /etc/nginx/nginx.conf | grep -A 10 's
erver {'
server {
    listen 80 default_server;
    listen [::]:80 default_server;

    root /home/user/app;
    index index.html index.htm index.nginx-debian.html;

    server_name _;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ =404;
    }

    location /secret {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8000/secret;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }
}

The nginx server configuration serves content from /home/user/app and proxies requests to /secret to a local Flask app on port 8000.

